  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both international and national levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) mechanisms\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Asset freezing and seizure\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Professional license revocation\n\n5. Regulated Sectors:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory and enforcement mechanisms.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
